Ahead of June 18, 2022, governorship election, the National Working Committee of the People’s Democratic Party has approved the nomination of five of its members to serve on the Ward Congresses Electoral Committee in Ekiti State. This is according to a statement signed late Friday by the Party’s National Organising Secretary, Umaru Bature, titled, ‘Ekiti State gubernatorial exercise: ward congresses electoral committee.’ According to Bature, the committee is mandated to conduct Party Congresses in the state to elect three Ad-Hoc ward delegates. The exercise is scheduled for Saturday, January 15, 2022, in all the 177 wards of the state. The committee constitutes Udom Emmanuel as Chairman, Michael Mku, Modinat Adedibu, Zanna Mustapha and Kola Ologbondiyan as Secretary.